## Context

Inspect `index.html` structure and CSS variables before edits. State section, conversion impact, and mobile behaviour change.

**Deep skills on demand:**
- **`.cursor/skills/designing-beautiful-websites/SKILL.md`** — conversion path, harness QA, landing checklist
- **`.agents/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md`** — palettes, a11y, UX rules (optional CLI if installed)

## Design tokens (source of truth: index.html)

- Colours: `--bg`, `--gold`, warm ivory editorial palette
- Layout: `--max`, `.wrap`, `.grid`, `.card`, `.portfolio-grid`
- Typography: Cormorant Garamond + Inter (Google Fonts)
- Breakpoints: **760px**, **1024px** (mobile-first)

## Page narrative (do not reorder without reason)

Hero → credibility strip → problem → offers → Rita's case study → portfolio → process → terms → FAQ → contact CTA.

## Images

- Paths: `assets/<name>.jpg` (plus `favicon.png`, `og-cover.jpg` for meta)
- Keep `onerror` fallbacks on hero and portfolio images
- Filenames must match `docs/image-shot-list.md` after changes

## Interaction

- `.reveal` + IntersectionObserver; honour `prefers-reduced-motion`
- `:focus-visible` outlines on links and buttons (already present — preserve)
- Sticky header + mobile `.sticky-cta` — do not break anchor navigation to `#contact`

## Accessibility baseline

- Contrast ≥4.5:1 body text; visible focus rings
- Semantic sections and heading hierarchy (`h1` once, logical `h2`/`h3`)
- Touch targets ≥44px where possible on primary CTAs

## Motion

- Prefer `transform` and `opacity` only
- No motion required to understand content
